--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[2026-04-14] ML strategy - single well / single schema first
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Decided / premised:
- Starting with ONE dataset (one well code such as F03-4, or one file) and ONE column
  schema family (7logs OR 6logs OR 3logs) is valid for a first ML pipeline: cleaning,
  train/val split, target variable, metrics, baseline.
- Data are NOT from a single well across the whole folder; prefixes F02, F03, F06
  indicate multiple origins. A model trained on one well may not generalize; treat
  multi-well claims only after held-out well test or grouped CV.
- If using stacked files (e.g. F02-1,F03-2,F06-1_*.txt), add well_id (or segment
  by known depth boundaries) so the model does not assume one stationary process.
- Next step for generalization: GroupKFold (or similar) by well_id, or reserve
  entire well(s) for test.

User confirmed: append this decision to agent.log (this entry).

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[2026-04-14] Target choice - porosity (current phase)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Decided:
- Primary ML target for now: porosity (Porosity column).
- 6logs TSV files do not include Porosity; use 7logs or 3logs for this target.
- Script: ML-prediction/scripts/porosity_baseline.py
  - HistGradientBoostingRegressor + StandardScaler on features.
  - Depth-ordered holdout: deepest test_fraction (default 0.2) as test set.
  - 7logs features: AC, Rho_b, AI, Vp, GR, Vc -> Porosity.
  - 3logs features: AC, GR -> Porosity; optional --clip-gr-nonnegative.

Example run (default file F03-4_7logs.txt): test MAE ~0.0005, R2 high; interpret
with care (elastic logs and porosity are strongly coupled in this data).

